{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> λῑτός</b>, ή, όν, <br /> <b>simple, inexpensive, frugal</b>, λιταὶ τράπεζαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD(?): Pseudo-Phocylidea 81; οἱ λ. χυλοί 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 3p.63U.; λ. βίος 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 633, 4th c.BC: Crates Thebanus Poeta Philosophus 10; τροφὴ λιτοτάτη 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 5.191f; λιτὴ δίαιτα 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.668f \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], compare 125d, etc.; τὸ λ. τῆς διαίτης, κατὰ τὴν δίαιταν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 478, 2nd c.AD: Marcus Antoninus Imperator 1.3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; παρέξοδος (which see) -οτέρη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ εὐσχημοσύνης” 8; λ. χλαμύδιον 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 442; τὰ ἱμάτια λ. καὶ σώφρονα 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Caesares” 317c; μίτρη λιτὴ στυππείου “Michel” 832.17 (Samos, 4th c.BC); ὑποκεφάλαια δύο ἡμιτυβίου λιτά [prev. work]l.23; [ἀσπίδας] χαλκᾶς λιτὰς δύο, opposed to περίχρυσος μία, “IG” 22.1491.31 (4th c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἅλα λιτὸν ἐπέσθων <b>frugal</b> salt, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Epigrammata” 48; λ. ὀξίς 4th c.BC: Nicostratus Comicus 9 (conjecture for λοιπή); λ. ὕδωρ πίνων 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 8.13 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; λ. χρίματα <b>simple</b> or <b>plain</b> unguents, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Lavacrum Palladis” 25; λ. ταφή 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “de Morte - Papiri Ercolanesi” 30 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; λ. ζωμός <b>thin</b> (chicken-) broth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 12.295 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; of medicines, ἡ διὰ κωδυῶν λιτή (i.e. δύναμις) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Crito Medicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 13.38; ἡ διὰ μόρων λιτή 2nd c.AD: Archigenes Medicus cited in [same work] 12.973; λ. ἔμπλαστροι 1st c.AD: Andromachus Poeta Medicus cited in [same work] 13.495, compare 486 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; χάρτης λιτός, as a cargo, perhaps <b>cheap</b> or <b>coarse</b> papyrus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Catalogus Codicum Astrologorum” 1.104.28. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of persons, <b>poor</b>, λ. γενόμενος τοῖς ἔχουσι μὴ φθόνει uncertain in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Dionysius Comicus 10 (= 4th c.BC: Dionysius Tragicus 8)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>frugal</b>, αὐτάρκεις καὶ λ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 6.48.7; κατὰ τὴν ἐσθῆτα καὶ σίτησιν ἀφελὴς καὶ λ. [prev. author] 11.10.3; λ. περὶ δίαιταν 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.709b. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i> -τῶς <b>frugally</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Sotades Comicus 1.6, “Anthologia Graeca” 7.156 (6th-7th c.AD: Isidorus Hispalensis Grammaticus); λ. βιοῦν 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 6.105; λ. καὶ σωφρόνως ζῆν 4th c.BC: Ephorus Historicus 149 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; λαμπρῶς ἢ λ. ἐξενεχθέντας Phld. [prev. cited] <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, of style, <b>plain, simple, unadorned</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1416b25, 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Thucydide” 23, +others \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>paltry, petty, small</b>, τάφος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 7.73 (Gemin.), compare 7.18 (1st c.BC: Antipater Thessalonicensis Epigrammaticus) \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; of persons, opposed to μέγας, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Apollinem” 10; πολισμάτια 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 32.8.3. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i> -τῶς <b>slightly</b>, ἡψημένα [<a href=\"javas